File: The Correctional Services Department says strict conditions will be attached to Bob Hewitt's release. JOHANNESBURG - Convicted rapist Bob Hewitt is being released from prison on Friday. The Correctional Services Department says strict conditions will be attached to his release. READ: Bob Hewitt's parole set aside In 2015, the tennis star was convicted for the rape of two young women and the sexual assault of another. He had coached all three women in the 80s and 90s. Hewitt was sentenced to six years in prison.